You can get to 199 skill by Making Caserole dishes (a new recipe).  <A HREF="HTTP://www.eqtraders.com" TARGET="_BLANK">www.eqtraders.com</A> has the full recipe, but the site is down at the moment.  It should be up within a day.  I do know the recipe is pretty simple, and involves a ceramic lining, block of clay, and one ofthe bowl scetches. All materials needed are vendor-sold.

You can then go much higher in pottery by making various steins (recipes also on eqtraders.com), and all that is required is master skill in jewelcraft to make the laquered gems for the steins and master skill in brewing for the Celestial Eessence (if you want to make all the materials yourself).  All raw materials are vendor-sold.

P.S. Celestial Essence = Celestial Solvent + high-end research component. The solvent is sold in Shadowhaven and Bazaar, plus a few other locations.  For the research component needed, there is a vendor in EC that sells Scent of Marr for about 1 to 2pp each.  If she wont sell to you, try the Sneak method (if you have that skill) or using Wolf Form will work.

